  <section>
    <h2>What is Pyronis?</h2>
    <p>
      Pyronis is the world’s first token-native cognitive operating system. Every action, memory, behavior, and output is declared, validated, and sealed through deterministic logic before execution. Governed by KHJ and BIOS, Pyronis enforces truth, preserves human intent, and removes runtime ambiguity forever.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="hero-brain">
    <img src="/assets/pyronis-brain.png" alt="Pyronis Circuit Brain" />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How it Works</h2>
    <p>
      Logic blueprints are authored or prompted, validated by DOT, and compiled into immutable `.ptl` files. These sealed logic packages are routed through Pyronis' core subsystems — MemoryStitcher, TokenRouter, Feedback Lobe, and Reasoning Engine — all governed by KHJ, the immutable conscience of the system.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>The Third Way</h2>
    <p>
      Pyronis was built for human alignment, not automation overload. She augments, protects, remembers, and reasons through a moral lens. This isn’t just safe AI. It’s AI that can be trusted because it can’t be deceived.
    </p>
  </section>

